<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="650" height="366" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Cart-Abandonment-Recipe.gif" alt="Cart Abandonment Recipe" class="wp-image-103250"/></figure></div>
</div></div>



<h2 id="Host-a-Giveaway"><strong>2. Host a Giveaway</strong></h2>



<p>Most of the purchases on your site will take more than one session to complete. That’s a given.<br></p>



<p>After all, first-time visitors aren’t always ready to buy.<br></p>



<p>Instead of asking them to buy on their first visit, you can ask them to take another action, such as leaving their email address in exchange for something valuable.<br></p>



<p>Hosting a giveaway is one effective way of getting more visitors to sign up to your email list—without spending a fortune on gifts or lowering the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/perceived-value" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">perceived value</a> of your products.<br></p>



<p>You might be thinking that <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/giveaway-ideas" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">on-site giveaways</a> are only useful for collecting email addresses.<br></p>



<p>And you would be right in thinking so. But giveaways are especially effective when promoted to visitors abandoning their cart.<br></p>



<p><a href="https://www.wallstickerland.dk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Wallstickerland</a> illustrates this well:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="369" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-1024x369.png" alt="Wallstickerland Giveaway Popup" class="wp-image-76434" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-1024x369.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-300x108.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-768x277.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-380x137.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-600x216.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-760x274.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-97x35.png 97w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-139x50.png 139w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-740x267.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-220x79.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup-385x139.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Wallstickerland-Giveaway-Popup.png 1173w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Translation: “Wait … Don’t miss out on our competition to win a gift card worth 1,000 DKK for Wallstickerland!”</em></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p>If you choose to leave your cart items behind, the company gently recommends you “not to miss out” on their giveaway.<br></p>



<p>This way, they trigger your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/fomo-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">fear-of-missing-out</a> (FOMO) and give you a strong reason to leave your email address.<br></p>



<p>Plus, they get warm leads that they can follow up on with both abandoned cart emails and <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/promotional-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">promotional emails</a> when their giveaway ends.<br></p>



<p>Another approach you can take is nudging your visitors to complete their purchase within a time limit in order to participate in your giveaway.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example of how that might look:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="562" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-1024x562.png" alt="Sleeknote Giveaway Example" class="wp-image-76426" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-1024x562.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-300x165.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-768x421.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-380x208.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-600x329.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-760x417.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-64x35.png 64w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-91x50.png 91w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-740x406.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-220x121.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example-385x211.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Giveaway-Example.png 1143w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>For these type of cart abandonment popups, a countdown timer is a must-have to drive a sense of urgency and <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/scarcity-marketing" target="_blank">scarcity</a>.</p>



<h2 id="Promote-Special-Offers"><strong>3. Promote Special Offers</strong></h2>



<p>Even though abandoning visitors are not ready to buy from you, they are already in the decision stage of your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-sales-funnel" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">sales funnel</a>. Why? Because they took an important step in becoming a customer by adding an item to their cart.<br></p>



<p>Maybe the timing or the price wasn’t right for them.<br></p>



<p>This means that even if they didn’t buy the product at this moment, they might be interested in the item in the future (especially if/when it goes on sale).<br></p>



<p>So why don’t you let them know when your next big sale is approaching?<br></p>



<p>That’s exactly what <a href="https://chubbiesshorts.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Chubbies</a> does when you’re about to abandon your cart:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="630" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-1024x630.png" alt="Chubbies Sale Popup" class="wp-image-76402" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-1024x630.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-300x184.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-768x472.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-380x234.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-600x369.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-760x467.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-57x35.png 57w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-81x50.png 81w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-740x455.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-220x135.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup-385x237.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Chubbies-Sale-Popup.png 1184w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>The company lets you know when the sale will take place and what you should expect from it, even if you’re not ready to buy at this point.<br></p>



<p>But here’s the twist: <em>They add a second layer of discounting to it if you place an order today.</em><br></p>



<p>If they had only announced the next big sale in their cart abandonment popup, it would delay your purchase rather than incentivize you to buy now. Why? Because if you know there’s a big sale approaching, why should you buy anything now?<br></p>



<p>That’s why if you complete your order today, they offer you an extra 15% on top of a big sale.<br></p>



<p>(And it sounds too good to miss.)<br></p>



<p>With this popup, Chubbies not only aims to reduce cart abandonment but also turn buyers into repeat customers.<br></p>



<p>If you want to use this strategy, you can improve this popup by;<br></p>



<ol><li>Focusing more on the benefit of completing the purchase <em>now, </em>instead of giving too many details about the upcoming sale;</li><li>Including a countdown timer to drive urgency;</li><li>Adding a benefit-driven <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/call-to-action" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">call-to-action</a> (CTA) button, such as “Claim Extra 15% Off.”</li></ol>



<h2 id="Personalize-Your-On-Site-Messages"><strong>4. Personalize Your On-Site Messages</strong></h2>



<p><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-personalization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Personalization</a> is no longer a luxury for e-commerce sites. <em>It’s a must.</em><br></p>



<p>Online consumers expect and desire a more personalized shopping experience and they’re <a href="https://www.accenture.com/us-en/service-propelling-growth-through-personalization" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">willing to share their data</a> in exchange for it.<br></p>



<p>Many e-commerce sites welcome their return visitors with personalized copy or make relevant <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/product-recommendations" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">product recommendations</a>. But few marketers go above and beyond to <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/personalized-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">personalize their on-site messages</a>.<br></p>



<p>We know from customer data, and our own experiences, that online stores that provide personalized offers achieve higher conversion rates.<br></p>



<p>By personalizing your cart abandonment popups, you can remind abandoning visitors what they are about to miss out on.<br></p>



<p>Here’s a brilliant cart abandonment popup example from <a href="https://us.pandora.net" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Pandora</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="489" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-1024x489.png" alt="Pandora Personalized Popup" class="wp-image-76418" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-1024x489.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-300x143.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-768x367.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-380x181.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-600x287.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-760x363.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-73x35.png 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-105x50.png 105w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-740x353.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-220x105.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup-385x184.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Pandora-Personalized-Popup.png 1229w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>When you add a product to your cart and go to leave their site before buying it, Pandora displays a popup with the picture of your cart item.<br></p>



<p>They also trigger your FOMO with the headline “Don’t miss out on this great style!”<br></p>



<p>Showing the number of people viewing that item, they both point to the product’s scarcity of availability and add <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/social-proof" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">social proof</a> to it.<br></p>



<p>Plus, they add a link button that reads “Find Your Local Store,” in case you want to visit a physical store and complete your purchase there.<br></p>



<p>Using the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/features/sitedata" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">SiteData</a> condition, you can personalize your cart abandonment popups based on the visitor’s basket items and convert them with a highly-relevant offer.<br></p>



<h2 id="Offer-an-Alternative"><strong>5. Offer an Alternative</strong></h2>



<p>Although clicking the “Add to Cart” button carries greater purchase intention, it doesn’t mean that the visitor is 100% sure about buying the product.<br></p>



<p>You might assume that your site visitors leave their carts due to reasons unrelated to your products:&nbsp;<br></p>



<ul><li>They don’t want to pay for shipping;&nbsp;</li><li>They’re not comfortable with giving you their credit card details;</li><li>They’re distracted by something else;</li><li>And so on.</li></ul>



<p>But what if the problem is directly related to your products?<br></p>



<p>Maybe the visitor couldn’t find what they were looking for and didn’t feel comfortable completing the purchase at this point.<br></p>



<p>Even if you provide your visitors a seamless <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-website-navigation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">site navigation</a>, you should still consider that they may not always find the right product for them. So try offering them an alternative solution, instead.<br></p>



<p>Here’s how <a href="https://sleeknote.com/success-stories/hojmark" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Højmark</a>, a Danish travel agency, does that:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="544" height="571" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup.jpg" alt="Hojmark Custom Quote Popup" class="wp-image-76406" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup.jpg 544w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-286x300.jpg 286w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-380x399.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-33x35.jpg 33w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-48x50.jpg 48w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-467x490.jpg 467w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-220x231.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Hojmark-Custom-Quote-Popup-385x404.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px" /></figure></div>



<p>Højmark knows that different visitors have different needs. Instead of letting go of the visitors who can’t find their ideal vacation, the company offers them a custom quote.<br></p>



<p>Setting this campaign to work on exit-intent, Højmark converts visitors who can’t find a vacation that fits their needs by suggesting them an alternative.<br></p>



<p>If you want to personalize your custom offers based on the users’ visiting behavior, you can use the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/features/sitedata" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">SiteData</a> condition.<br></p>



<p>If a visitor adds items to their cart from a certain category before leaving your site, you can customize the contact form to fit their needs.<br></p>



<p>For example, if a visitor has cart items in the hiking category, you can frame the campaign copy as “Let our team of hiking experts offer you a custom quote…”<br></p>



<p>This type of cart abandonment campaign especially works well if you’re selling expensive products, offering wholesale, or handling custom orders.<br></p>



<h2 id="Convert-Abandoning-Visitors-Into-Warm-Leads"><strong>6. Convert Abandoning Visitors Into Warm Leads</strong></h2>



<p>You might think that the only purpose of cart abandonment popups is to convince your visitors to stay on your site and to complete their purchase as soon as possible.<br></p>



<p>And you’re not wrong in thinking that.<br></p>



<p>In an ideal world, you would capture and convince all of your abandoning visitors to buy from you. But in reality, it takes more than that.<br></p>



<p>If you convince abandoning visitors to leave their email addresses, you can target them later with highly specific email campaigns. But in order to do this, you need to give them a valid reason to opt in.<br></p>



<p>Frame your campaign copy around the benefit you provide your visitors in exchange and they’ll be more likely to opt in.<br></p>



<p>Many e-commerce marketers use <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/discount-strategy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">discount codes</a> as an incentive and it surely is a great offer. But how can you stand out if everybody else is doing it?<br></p>



<p>Maybe you want to try something else or maybe you can’t afford to discount your products.<br></p>



<p>Luckily, there’s another value you can offer to abandoning visitors: <em>saving their cart.</em><br></p>



<p>Here’s how your campaign might look like:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="843" height="478" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup.png" alt="Save Your Cart Popup" class="wp-image-76422" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup.png 843w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-300x170.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-768x435.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-380x215.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-600x340.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-760x431.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-62x35.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-88x50.png 88w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-740x420.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-220x125.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Save-Your-Cart-Popup-385x218.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px" /></figure></div>



<p>There are multiple reasons why online shoppers abandon their carts and lack of time is among the most common reasons.<br></p>



<p>Offering your abandoning visitors to save their cart will help you <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/list-building-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">build an email list</a> with warm leads that you can target with personalized email campaigns.<br></p>



<p>Make sure you hide this campaign from your existing subscribers so that they don’t see an invite to join a list that they’re already in.<br></p>



<h2 id="Ask-for-Feedback"><strong>7. Ask for Feedback</strong></h2>



<p>You’re likely working hard to collect valuable feedback from your customers and trying new methods to get positive <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/customer-testimonials" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">testimonials</a>.<br></p>



<p>But oftentimes, the critical feedback you need to grow your business will come from unsatisfied prospects.<br></p>



<p>If a visitor is leaving your site after adding an item to their basket, that’s a problem you need to work on.<br></p>



<p>And if you never ask, you’ll never know.<br></p>



<p>Asking short and simple questions to abandoning visitors can help you collect valuable insights on why your visitors leave their carts on checkout pages.<br></p>



<p>If you’re suffering from high cart abandonment rates or if you want to improve your conversions, try running a campaign where you ask your visitors why they’re leaving.<br></p>



<p>This way, you can find out the biggest barriers to purchase on your online store and use those insights in your cart abandonment popups.<br></p>



<p>Take this example by <a href="https://www.novasol.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Novasol</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="993" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-993x1024.jpg" alt="Novasol Feedback Popup" class="wp-image-76414" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-993x1024.jpg 993w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-291x300.jpg 291w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-768x792.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-380x392.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-600x619.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-760x784.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-34x35.jpg 34w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-48x50.jpg 48w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-475x490.jpg 475w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-220x227.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup-385x397.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Novasol-Feedback-Popup.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 993px) 100vw, 993px" /></figure></div>



<p>When Novasol ran this campaign on their site, they gathered <strong>more than 18,000 responses.</strong><br></p>



<p>Why?<br></p>



<ul><li>The form is easy-to-fill with a limited number of input fields and radio buttons.</li><li>The company doesn’t ask for any personal information, such as name or email address, and makes it clear that all answers are anonymous. This way, visitors feel more comfortable about giving their honest opinion without being targeted with email campaigns later.</li></ul>



<p>Add a URL condition to make sure your campaign is only visible on relevant pages, such as your checkout page, and show it only to abandoning visitors by using the exit-intent condition.<br></p>


